<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="28" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="28">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="28">
Given the geographical proximity, it is possible that the 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Buthus" order="Scorpiones" pageId="13" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Buthus</taxonomicName>
material reported to have been found in Guinea-Bissau might very well correspond to this species. Unfortunately the Guinea-Bissau material was lost in a fire, and hence only newly collected material could confirm this possibility.
</paragraph>
